Changelog

All notable changes and troubleshooting steps for this project are documented here.

[v0.1] - Initial Setup
Created initial Bash script structure
Attempted to parse /var/log/auth.log
Issue: File not found on Linux Mint

[v0.2] - Logging Investigation
Discovered system uses journalctl instead of traditional log files
Verified logs using:
-journalctl | wc -l
-journalctl | grep -i pam
Identified PAM logs as primary authentication source

[v0.3] - Script Debugging
Issue: Script returned empty output despite logs existing
Root cause:
-Pattern mismatch (Failed password not present)
-Variable-based log storage caused failures
Fix:
-Switched to direct piping instead of variables
-Broadened grep filters (failure, pam, etc.)

[v0.4] - Functional Version
Script successfully:
-Counts authentication events
-Identifies failure patterns
-Outputs recent log activity
Confirmed working on Linux Mint

Future Improvements
-Extract usernames from authentication logs
-Add IP parsing (if available)
-Implement real-time monitoring (journalctl -f)
-Add alerting for repeated failures
